  "script": "Monkeys are kidnapping babies, and not even their own kind. On an island off Panama, scientists watching capuchin monkeys noticed something that made no sense: young males were carrying around baby howler monkeys, a completely different species. It started with one monkey. Then others copied him, like a trend spreading through the group. The babies weren't being adopted; most didn't survive, because capuchins can't feed them. Researchers think it's a cultural fad, a pointless habit passed monkey to monkey, the way a dance goes viral with us. It's one of the only times we've seen animals invent a tradition that actually hurts them. So what makes a whole group copy something this strange?",
